            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <a class="w3-button w3-black w3-display-right w3-margin-right w3-round w3-hide-small w3-hover-light-grey"
       onclick="plusDivs(1)">See more <i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i></a>
    <a class="w3-button w3-block w3-black w3-hide-large w3-hide-medium" onclick="plusDivs(1)">See more <i
            class="fa fa-angle-right"></i></a>
</header>

<!-- The App Section -->
<div class="w3-padding-64 w3-white">
    <div class="w3-row-padding">
        <div class="w3-col l8 m6">
            <h1 class="w3-jumbo"><b>Chef On Phone</b></h1>
            <h1 class="w3-xxxlarge w3-text-green"><b>Why use it?</b></h1>
            <p>
                <span class="w3-xlarge">Code like a pro.</span> With this app you can utilise all your travel time and
                use codechef anywhere you go.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>See ongoing/future contests.</li>
                <li>View all contests and practice problems.</li>
                <li>Solve the problems on their phone and run to see the results.</li>
                <li>Download their solution to make submission on codechef.</li>
                <li>Set reminders for future contests on codechef.</li>
                <li>Access saved problem statements and work offline.</li>

            </ul>
            <a href="{{ apk_url }}" title="Download">
                <button class="w3-button w3-light-grey w3-padding-large w3-section">
                    <i class="fa fa-download"></i> Download Application
                </button>
            </a>
            <p>Available for <i class="fa fa-android w3-xlarge w3-text-green"></i></p>
        </div>
        <div class="w3-col l4 m6">
            <img src="/images/logo.png" class="w3-image w3-right w3-hide-small" width="335" height="471">

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Footer -->
<footer class="w3-container w3-padding-32 w3-light-grey w3-center w3-xlarge">
    <p class="w3-medium">Copyright&copy; 2018 Chef On Phone | Powered by codechef</p>
</footer>

<script>
    // Slideshow
    var slideIndex = 1;
    showDivs(slideIndex);

    function plusDivs(n) {
        showDivs(slideIndex += n);
    }

    function showDivs(n) {
        var i;
        var x = document.getElementsByClassName("mySlides");
        if (n > x.length) {
            slideIndex = 1
        }
        if (n < 1) {
            slideIndex = x.length
        }
        for (i = 0; i < x.length; i++) {
            x[i].style.display = "none";
        }
        x[slideIndex - 1].style.display = "block";
    }
</script>

</body>
</html>